-- GE sees Q2 profit down at finance units
-- 
-- Fri Apr 11, 2008 8:30am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/11/us-ge-outlook-idUSN1132252720080411

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - General Electric Co said on Friday it expects second-quarter profit to decline at its financial units. 

 The company expects profit at its GE Money consumer finance arm to be down 20 percent and at its commercial finance arm to be down 10 percent. It forecast profit would rise 20 percent or more at the infrastructure unit and 5 percent at the health care, industrial and NBC Universal units, the U.S conglomerate said in slides posted to its Web site ahead of a conference call with analysts. (Reporting by  Scott Malone , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)